1.
When converting ANY number to another base:

Take remainder → that becomes the digit.
Divide → continue.
Reverse at the end.

This pattern works for: ( binary, hex, octal, ANY base )

2.
To get -X:

Flip bits
+1

3.
Study in this order:
Binary number system (base-2, decimal ↔ binary conversion)
Signed vs unsigned integers
Two’s complement (negative number representation)
Bitwise operators: &, |, ^, ~
Shift operators: <<, >>, >>>
Bit masking (set, clear, toggle, check bits)
Power-of-two pattern (n & (n-1))
Base conversions using bits (binary ↔ hex, etc.)
Counting set bits (Hamming weight)
Common bit tricks used in coding problems